captivating bird whistler.

16:15.392 --> 16:18.561
-Hey, everybody.
-All right, Tommy!

16:18.603 --> 16:20.897
Uh, Lonnie put me up
to this shit.

16:22.399 --> 16:24.901
Uh, I'm not gonna
whistle for you.

16:24.943 --> 16:26.403
I'm, uh... I'm gonna
tell you a story.

16:26.444 --> 16:29.155
-Ghosts and goblins!
-Oh...

16:30.407 --> 16:32.867
-- You got this, Tommy!
-- Turn off the lights!

16:32.909 --> 16:36.538
Any of you know the story
of the Haddonfield Boogeyman?

16:36.579 --> 16:40.208
Too young to give a shit?
Too drunk to remember?

16:40.250 --> 16:45.046
40 years ago, a madman escaped
from a mental hospital.

16:45.088 --> 16:47.090
It was the night
before Halloween,

16:47.132 --> 16:48.925
and three teenage girls

16:48.967 --> 16:50.844
were walking home
from Haddonfield High.

16:50.885 --> 16:53.555
They had sightings of a...

16:53.596 --> 16:57.225
a ghostlike figure creeping
right through our town.

16:57.267 --> 17:00.103
A man in a white mask.

17:00.145 --> 17:03.023
Or was it more than a man?

17:03.064 --> 17:05.442
He was watching them.

17:05.483 --> 17:09.487
Before the night was over,
three people would be murdered.

17:09.529 --> 17:13.158
And in the house next door,
there was a babysitter

17:13.199 --> 17:15.660
and a young boy
and a young girl,

17:15.702 --> 17:18.997
and they were brutally attacked
by this stalker

17:19.039 --> 17:23.335
who had a power beyond
any mortal man.

17:25.378 --> 17:27.881
My name is Tommy Doyle.

17:28.840 --> 17:31.134
And I was that young boy.

17:31.176 --> 17:34.888
So, please, join me

17:34.929 --> 17:38.600
in commemorating the victims

17:38.641 --> 17:42.437
and the survivors
of Michael Myers.

17:42.479 --> 17:45.231
-Thank you.

17:48.318 --> 17:52.781
Now, we have, uh, the lovely
Miss Lindsey Wallace.

17:52.822 --> 17:56.659
