43:05.168 --> 43:08.088
He is stalking her, and we are
staying here to protect her.

43:08.129 --> 43:10.757
He's infected your family,
he's infected my family

43:10.799 --> 43:12.884
with grief and fear
for 40 years.

43:12.926 --> 43:14.511
He's gonna die tonight.

43:14.552 --> 43:16.388
-He killed Dad. -Clear
the hallway! You have to move!

43:16.429 --> 43:18.765
Excuse me! My husband,
he's been very badly hurt!

43:18.807 --> 43:20.558
-Clear the hallway, people.

43:20.600 --> 43:22.143
Go back to the waiting area.

43:22.185 --> 43:24.646
Go back to the waiting room.
Clear the hallway.

43:24.688 --> 43:27.315
I'm not gonna pretend
this didn't happen.

43:27.357 --> 43:29.109
I love Dad, and somebody loves

43:29.150 --> 43:32.195
whoever is laying
under those sheets right now.

43:33.446 --> 43:35.949
Look. Look at me.
We failed, baby.

43:35.990 --> 43:38.076
We set a trap,
we set the whole thing on fire,

43:38.118 --> 43:39.953
and he lived through it.
Think about that.

43:39.994 --> 43:42.080
The police are out there
looking for him.

43:42.122 --> 43:44.708
You think you're the one
that's gonna find him?

43:44.749 --> 43:48.169
Sit in that room
and wait with your grandmother.

43:48.211 --> 43:49.879
Now!

43:54.634 --> 43:56.594
Does the hospital have
security guards?

43:56.636 --> 43:58.138
Do you have security guards?

43:58.179 --> 43:59.889
It seems like you should have
security guards

43:59.931 --> 44:01.891
in case something
like this happens.

44:01.933 --> 44:03.560
And this is happening right now.

44:03.601 --> 44:06.521
I mean, my daughter is in here,
my mother is in here,

44:06.563 --> 44:08.773
there is a madman
on the loose...

44:08.815 --> 44:10.734
Oh! Oh, God!

44:18.575 --> 44:20.118
Goodbye, Michael.

44:52.692 --> 44:56.029
This is for you,
whenever you need it.

45:13.588 --> 45:15.924
She's here. She's here.
We found her. Laurie's here.

45:15.965 --> 45:18.426
She's in recovery.

45:18.468 --> 45:19.803
It's lucky she survived.

45:19.844 --> 45:21.554
I just heard from
one of the police officers

45:21.596 --> 45:22.972
at her compound.

45:23.014 --> 45:25.100
11 dead bodies.
They're all first responders.

45:25.141 --> 45:27.018
Holy shit.
Cameron's in there.

45:27.060 --> 45:29.020
Three of his friends
were killed.

45:29.062 --> 45:30.772
-It's a madhouse.
-All right, Lonnie, listen.

45:30.814 --> 45:32.857
The only way
we're gonna stop this

45:32.899 --> 45:34.818
is if we all come together
on this.

45:34.859 --> 45:36.069
You're goddamn right.

45:36.111 --> 45:37.821
-All right. All right.
-All right?

45:39.739 --> 45:42.158
How about this sassy tackle?

45:43.702 --> 45:45.161
You have a permit for all these?

45:45.203 --> 45:46.246
Some of 'em.

45:46.287 --> 45:48.873
-- Dad.
-- Hey, hey.

45:50.166 --> 45:52.085
-Where's your girlfriend?
-Uh, she's okay.

45:52.127 --> 45:53.920
-She's gonna stay
with her family. -Good for her.

45:53.962 --> 45:55.505
-Hey, Mr. Doyle.
-Hey, buddy.

45:55.547 --> 45:57.882
-Lonnie, check it out.

46:00.969 --> 46:03.013
You guys are coming, too?

46:03.054 --> 46:04.472
Couldn't let you have
all the fun.

46:04.514 --> 46:06.224
So many victims
in our neighborhood.

46:06.266 --> 46:07.726
Close friends of ours,
and we just want to help out.

46:07.767 --> 46:08.977
I'm a doctor.
My husband's a nurse.

46:09.019 --> 46:10.603
I should've guessed.

46:10.645 --> 46:12.439
All right, we have to give all
these people protection.

46:12.480 --> 46:14.149
-You got to share your shit,
Lonnie. -All right.

46:14.190 --> 46:16.067
You coming with us?

46:16.109 --> 46:18.111
Let's see what you got.

46:18.153 --> 46:20.030
Yeah, just help yourself.

46:21.531 --> 46:24.993
Michael Myers has haunted
this town for 40 years.

46:26.703 --> 46:28.496
Tonight, we hunt him down.

46:34.377 --> 46:36.504
Excuse me.
I need some good people.

46:36.546 --> 46:38.548
People who aren't afraid
to get their hands dirty.

46:38.590 --> 46:40.258
Everybody else needs to go home.

46:42.052 --> 46:44.054
So, what do we do
if we find him?

46:44.095 --> 46:45.764
Go inside. Go inside.

46:45.805 --> 46:47.515
It's not safe to be out. Go.

46:47.557 --> 46:49.059
It's not safe to be out.

46:49.100 --> 46:51.728
Man, I had an altercation
with Myers about an hour ago,

46:51.770 --> 46:53.271
but he escaped.

46:53.313 --> 46:55.023
Now, listen, boys,
there's strength in numbers.

46:55.065 --> 46:57.108
You cover Spring Creek
to the bypass,

46:57.150 --> 46:59.152
and then let me know
if you see anything.

46:59.194 --> 47:02.280
This man is a threat,
and we need to stop him tonight!

47:03.865 --> 47:05.867
Nobody ever took him seriously.

47:05.909 --> 47:07.660
-Who?
-Dr. Loomis,

47:07.702 --> 47:09.704
Michael's first doctor.

47:09.746 --> 47:11.373
He knew a killer
when he saw one.

47:11.414 --> 47:13.291
Now, the only way to catch him

47:13.333 --> 47:16.044
is to play by his own game--
the element of surprise.

47:16.086 --> 47:17.837
So he thinks
you're going one place,

47:17.879 --> 47:20.090
then you pop up someplace else.

47:20.131 --> 47:22.092
And keep your eyes open.

47:24.844 --> 47:26.054
Eyes open.

47:31.434 --> 47:33.728
Wait, what's going on
over there?

47:33.770 --> 47:35.605
Baby, who is that?

47:35.647 --> 47:37.649
Looks like kids.

47:37.691 --> 47:39.150
They all alone?

47:39.192 --> 47:41.277
Marion, give me the flashlight.

47:41.319 --> 47:43.405
It's the wrong night to be out.

47:43.446 --> 47:44.572
Careful, Lindsey.

47:44.614 --> 47:46.324
-Lindsey, I wouldn't go...
-Stay here.

47:49.786 --> 47:51.413
Never fired a gun before.

47:51.454 --> 47:53.915
Right, so I don't even know
why they gave you a gun.

47:53.957 --> 47:55.792
It's big, too.
Can you handle it?

47:55.834 --> 47:57.085
-That's a no.

47:57.127 --> 47:58.253
Give me, give me.
I shot this shit before.

47:58.294 --> 47:59.754
Okay. If you want it.

47:59.796 --> 48:00.839
I got it.

48:00.880 --> 48:02.632
Okay. Fine.

48:04.759 --> 48:06.469
Hey.

48:06.511 --> 48:08.430
What are you guys
doing out here?

48:08.471 --> 48:10.265
It's Halloween.
We've been trick-or-treating.

48:10.306 --> 48:11.850
-We got a whole bag of candy.
-You guys should not be

48:11.891 --> 48:13.226
out here right now, okay?
It's not safe.

48:13.268 --> 48:14.436
-You gonna kill me?
-CHRISTY No.

48:14.477 --> 48:15.603
Satan, not today.

48:15.645 --> 48:17.772
-Oh, I'm so scared.
-Are you guys alone?

48:17.814 --> 48:19.315
-Where are your parents?
-No.

48:19.357 --> 48:21.026
No, we're waiting
for our friend.

48:21.067 --> 48:22.652
And, like, there's
a creepy man in a white mask,

48:22.694 --> 48:25.405
and he keeps, like, trying
to play hide-and-seek with us,

48:25.447 --> 48:27.615
-and he thinks...
-And I think he's a pervert.

48:27.657 --> 48:28.908
Where did you see him?

48:28.950 --> 48:30.160
He's just hiding behind trees.

48:30.201 --> 48:31.286
And he pops out like,
"Peekaboo!"

48:31.327 --> 48:32.954
I mean, we're not
three years old.

48:32.996 --> 48:34.289
-Come on, man!
-Oh, look, there he is.

48:34.330 --> 48:37.000
-Oh, hello!
-Hello.

48:37.042 --> 48:39.044
MINDY
What the hell are you doing?

48:40.837 --> 48:43.006
You want some candy?

48:45.675 --> 48:47.552
Is that Dennis's mask?

48:47.594 --> 48:49.262
Run. Go home now.

48:49.304 --> 48:51.306
Before he kills us all!
Get out of here!

48:51.348 --> 48:53.141
Run! Do not turn around!

48:53.183 --> 48:55.060
Keep going home!

48:56.019 --> 48:57.395
Oh, my God.

48:57.437 --> 48:59.314
What if someone is disabled?

48:59.356 --> 49:01.149
-Like, that doesn't make any
sense... -Yeah, but...

49:01.191 --> 49:03.068
-What the hell is that?

49:03.109 --> 49:04.778
-What the fuck?
-It's Michael.

49:09.366 --> 49:11.659
Fuck this bullshit! Drive!

49:11.701 --> 49:13.161
Go! Go!

49:22.128 --> 49:23.755
Drive the fucking...

49:25.507 --> 49:26.841
God!

49:28.718 --> 49:31.096
-No, whoa! Jesus, Marion.
-Marion, watch it!

49:35.558 --> 49:37.143
-Marion, the door's locked!
-I don't want to die in here!

49:37.185 --> 49:38.687
-Unlock the door!
-Unlock the door! -Oh!

49:38.728 --> 49:40.605
-Come on! -Let me out of here!
-Move! He's behind you!

49:40.647 --> 49:42.691
-The door's locked, Marion.
-Move!

49:47.404 --> 49:48.530
Go, go!

49:48.571 --> 49:49.364
Vanessa, go!

49:49.406 --> 49:51.282
Get out of the fucking car!

49:51.324 --> 49:54.077
-I love you, baby!

49:54.119 --> 49:56.454
No!

49:56.496 --> 49:58.540
-Let go of her!

49:59.582 --> 50:02.168
-Okay, come on. We got to go.
We got to go. -Oh, God.

50:03.753 --> 50:06.214
MARION
No.

50:06.256 --> 50:07.757
Shoot him! Shoot him, Marion!

50:07.799 --> 50:09.217
Hey, Michael.

50:09.259 --> 50:11.553
This is for Dr. Loomis.

50:19.060 --> 50:21.187
-Oh, God. No!
-Marion!

50:30.613 --> 50:32.949
Come on. Die.

50:32.991 --> 50:35.744
Die, die, die!

53:27.916 --> 53:30.418
-Mom. Oh, God. No, wait.

53:30.460 --> 53:33.088
Stop, stop, please.
Take it easy. Take it easy.

53:33.129 --> 53:34.631
-I'm fine.
-You're not fine.

53:34.673 --> 53:37.467
You had a knife
in your fucking stomach.

53:37.509 --> 53:39.803
It's a paper cut.

53:39.844 --> 53:41.763
Where's Allyson?

53:42.889 --> 53:45.350
She was supposed
to be in here, with you.

53:45.392 --> 53:47.268
-You didn't see her?
-Nah...

53:47.310 --> 53:49.813
I'm so geeked out
on pain meds, kiddo.

53:49.854 --> 53:52.315
Uh, uh, no.

53:55.235 --> 53:56.820
Is everything okay?

53:58.780 --> 54:00.699
She probably just needed
some fresh air.

54:03.076 --> 54:06.830
My God, they just leave your
bloody shirt just sitting here?

54:09.165 --> 54:11.042
Karen.

54:12.085 --> 54:14.337
Karen.

54:15.338 --> 54:17.507
Michael's gone.

54:18.341 --> 54:20.010
We got him.

54:20.051 --> 54:21.803
That's right. We got him.

54:21.845 --> 54:25.598
We burned him
to the goddamn ground.

54:25.640 --> 54:27.934
-Excuse us.

54:27.976 --> 54:30.186
Pardon.

54:30.228 --> 54:31.771
-Uh, over here.
-Frank?

54:31.813 --> 54:33.982
-- Go a little further back.
-- Okay. Okay.

54:34.024 --> 54:35.316
-Got the draw sheet?
-Yeah.

54:35.358 --> 54:36.651
One, two...

54:36.693 --> 54:38.236
-There you go.

54:38.278 --> 54:39.696
Okay.

54:41.239 --> 54:43.033
You knew my dad?

54:43.074 --> 54:45.368
Yeah, I knew Ray.

54:45.410 --> 54:48.329
He used to sell me peyote.

54:48.371 --> 54:52.542
I remember once we were out
on Lake Cherokee in this canoe

54:52.584 --> 54:55.003
with a shaman from Little Rock.

54:55.045 --> 54:58.923
Your-your daddy got freaked out

54:58.965 --> 55:00.759
by his own reflection.

55:00.800 --> 55:03.303
He took off his pants,
and he jumped in.

55:05.096 --> 55:07.515
I stopped doing drugs with him,

55:07.557 --> 55:10.393
but I'll-I'll miss him.

55:10.435 --> 55:12.228
-- Dad.
-- What? It's true.

55:12.270 --> 55:14.314
No, no, no.
Dad, look, right there.

55:14.356 --> 55:16.608
You see that? That's Tommy.

55:16.649 --> 55:19.069
-- Yeah.
-- Whose car is that?

55:19.110 --> 55:21.404
Lindsey's. Shit.

55:25.075 --> 55:26.534
Lindsey's car.

55:26.576 --> 55:28.453
It's covered in blood.
There's no bodies.

55:28.495 --> 55:30.413
It's Michael.

55:30.455 --> 55:32.248
He's here.

55:32.290 --> 55:34.584
Come on, I need you guys.
Come on.

55:34.626 --> 55:35.794
Be careful now, all right?

55:35.835 --> 55:37.212
Keep your heads up, eyes open.

55:37.253 --> 55:38.880
Okay. Let's go, let's go.

55:39.631 --> 55:41.383
Lindsey!

55:41.424 --> 55:43.593
-- Okay.
-- Just be safe, okay?

55:43.635 --> 55:45.428
You, too. Lindsey!

55:45.470 --> 55:47.555
Lindsey!

55:50.058 --> 55:51.393
Lindsey!

55:51.434 --> 55:53.436
-- Marion!
-- Marion!

55:57.357 --> 55:59.192
You guys be careful, okay?

55:59.234 --> 56:00.902
Keep your heads up.

56:02.404 --> 56:04.614
Oh, shit, Tommy.

56:08.284 --> 56:10.453
Oh, fuck.

56:15.458 --> 56:17.168
Oh, God.

56:33.143 --> 56:34.686
Fuck me.

56:34.728 --> 56:36.604
Yo, Dad, Dad.
What's over there?

56:36.646 --> 56:38.857
We found something.

56:39.983 --> 56:41.776
Oh, God.

56:44.487 --> 56:47.115
Oh, I'm sorry.

56:47.157 --> 56:49.617
-That's Marion, Lonnie.
-He did this.

56:49.659 --> 56:52.620
Oh, God, Marion.

56:52.662 --> 56:55.248
Tommy, what the fuck?

56:55.290 --> 56:58.001
I'm gonna get you.

56:58.043 --> 57:00.503
Come and get it, man.

57:07.135 --> 57:08.511
Over here.

57:08.553 --> 57:10.764
She's over here.

57:10.805 --> 57:13.350
LINDSEY
I saw his face.

57:13.391 --> 57:14.559
I saw everything.

57:14.601 --> 57:15.810
He's still out there.

57:15.852 --> 57:17.395
-She's lucky to be alive.
-I saw him.

57:17.437 --> 57:18.646
You saw his face?

57:18.688 --> 57:20.815
He's still out there, Tommy.

57:20.857 --> 57:22.817
You'll be okay, Lindsey.

57:22.859 --> 57:24.361
You're gonna be okay.

57:24.402 --> 57:26.988
He's still out there.

57:30.158 --> 57:32.035
Frank.

57:34.329 --> 57:36.289
Frank, are you awake?

57:43.713 --> 57:46.549
Do you remember that night?

57:46.591 --> 57:48.885
At the bar?

57:50.095 --> 57:52.389
You know, I-I never
said anything,

57:52.430 --> 57:54.766
'cause I couldn't be sure.

57:57.602 --> 57:59.938
I was so messed up.

58:07.070 --> 58:09.030
But you helped me.

58:13.076 --> 58:14.911
I always liked you.

58:17.997 --> 58:20.875
-You so crazy.

58:20.917 --> 58:22.877
Fuck you.

58:26.047 --> 58:27.590
Hi.

58:28.425 --> 58:30.593
Hi.

58:32.387 --> 58:34.305
I remember that night.

58:34.347 --> 58:36.141
Yeah.

58:37.767 --> 58:39.561
I kissed you.

58:39.602 --> 58:41.563
Yeah.

58:41.604 --> 58:43.440
I remember.

58:43.481 --> 58:45.734
You held my hand.

58:47.110 --> 58:48.903
That was it.

58:48.945 --> 58:51.823
Now, I was hoping for more.

58:53.366 --> 58:56.453
But I knew you were sweet for...

58:58.580 --> 59:00.832
Ben Tramer.

59:06.004 --> 59:07.380
Frank.

59:10.383 --> 59:12.218
We got him.

59:13.261 --> 59:15.805
We killed Michael.

59:16.598 --> 59:18.391
You ki...

59:21.186 --> 59:23.146
Well, it's about time.

59:23.188 --> 59:24.939
Ow.

59:24.981 --> 59:27.567
-Ow. Don't make me laugh.

59:27.609 --> 59:30.028
Oh, good. You're awake.

59:31.863 --> 59:33.698
Now, on a scale from one to ten,

59:33.740 --> 59:36.493
what is your pain level,
with ten being the worst?

59:36.534 --> 59:37.994
Number 11.

59:38.870 --> 59:40.538
This will make the pain go away.

59:42.999 --> 59:44.292
Laurie.

59:44.334 --> 59:47.087
Nurse, will you do me a favor?

59:47.879 --> 59:49.631
Help out my friend here.

59:49.673 --> 59:52.217
Make it a double.

59:52.258 --> 59:54.719
You stood up to that monster.

59:54.761 --> 59:56.763
I tried, Tommy.

59:56.805 --> 59:58.807
You know, when we were kids,

59:58.848 --> 1:00:00.809
we used to all dare each other

1:00:00.850 --> 1:00:02.811
to sneak into
the old Myers house.

1:00:04.354 --> 1:00:07.649
Lonnie was the only one
brave enough to do it.

1:00:07.691 --> 1:00:09.442
I lied.

1:00:10.527 --> 1:00:13.321
I never made it inside.

1:00:13.363 --> 1:00:15.407
When they arrested
Michael that night,

1:00:15.448 --> 1:00:18.076
I was telling my wife
that my daughter was killed,

1:00:18.118 --> 1:00:21.079
so I wasn't there to put
a bullet in his brain,

1:00:21.121 --> 1:00:23.164
like we should have.
This is no time for prudence.

1:00:23.206 --> 1:00:25.500
How'm I supposed to know
if my brother's alive or not?

1:00:25.542 --> 1:00:27.752
-I-I don't know. -I've been
waiting here for over an hour.

1:00:27.794 --> 1:00:29.713
Who the hell's in charge here?

1:00:29.754 --> 1:00:31.256
Authorized medical
and security personnel only.

1:00:31.297 --> 1:00:33.008
There's not enough medical
or security help.

1:00:33.049 --> 1:00:34.509
-He's going to kill everybody!
-You need to relax.

1:00:34.551 --> 1:00:36.094
We've requested backup officers
and medical staff

1:00:36.136 --> 1:00:37.595
from Russellville
and Eaton County for support,

1:00:37.637 --> 1:00:38.930
but no confirmation.

1:00:38.972 --> 1:00:40.849
We can't handle
this scope a crime scene.

1:00:40.890 --> 1:00:42.892
My son.
My son Oscar, is he here?

1:00:42.934 --> 1:00:44.060
Uh, I got a call.

1:00:44.102 --> 1:00:45.770
I'm his mother. Is he alive?

1:00:45.812 --> 1:00:47.147
I have no idea, but triage
expansion just opened up.

1:00:47.188 --> 1:00:48.648
I'm gonna have you sign in
right here.

1:00:48.690 --> 1:00:50.025
It's spelled B-E-R-L-U-C-C-H-I.

1:00:50.066 --> 1:00:51.443
Clear the hallway, please.

1:00:51.484 --> 1:00:52.485
Somebody help!

1:00:52.527 --> 1:00:53.862
Please, emergency.

1:00:53.903 --> 1:00:55.030
Take her to
the emergency room, please.

1:00:55.071 --> 1:00:56.614
You're gonna be okay, Linds.

1:00:56.656 --> 1:00:57.907
He's still out there, Tommy.

1:00:57.949 --> 1:00:59.659
-Be careful.
-Karen.

1:00:59.701 --> 1:01:01.411
How are you doing?
How's your mom?

1:01:01.453 --> 1:01:02.954
-How's Laurie? Is she okay?
-Where's my daughter?

1:01:02.996 --> 1:01:04.372
She's okay. She's fine.

1:01:04.414 --> 1:01:05.457
She's with Lonnie and Cameron.

1:01:05.498 --> 1:01:06.666
No, no, but he's coming here.

1:01:06.708 --> 1:01:07.959
She's not supposed
to be with them.

1:01:08.001 --> 1:01:09.919
He's coming here?
How do you know that?

1:01:09.961 --> 1:01:12.797
All right, secure a perimeter.
Hospital's on lockdown.

1:01:12.839 --> 1:01:15.383
-All right, listen, folks.
Listen! -

1:01:15.425 --> 1:01:16.885
Folks, please.

1:01:16.926 --> 1:01:18.553
-The Boogeyman is at large.

1:01:18.595 --> 1:01:21.389
He's got no choice
but to emerge.

1:01:21.431 --> 1:01:23.224
He is an apex predator.

1:01:23.266 --> 1:01:25.560
When he surfaces,
there will be no pause.

1:01:25.602 --> 1:01:27.062
There will be no empathy.

1:01:27.103 --> 1:01:29.731
This ends when Michael is dead!

1:01:29.773 --> 1:01:31.941
