1:21:01.611 --> 1:21:03.738
Pete went for his gun.

1:21:03.780 --> 1:21:06.700
As he pulled it up, it went off.

1:21:08.910 --> 1:21:11.037
Give me your gun.

1:21:11.871 --> 1:21:13.206
Don't look at it.

1:21:13.248 --> 1:21:16.001
Just be cool
and give me your gun.

1:21:16.042 --> 1:21:18.086
Take this.

1:21:18.128 --> 1:21:19.921
It was an accident.

1:21:19.963 --> 1:21:21.589
He shot himself.

1:21:21.631 --> 1:21:23.299
Got it?

1:21:24.134 --> 1:21:25.427
Just because
your intentions are good

1:21:25.468 --> 1:21:27.637
doesn't mean things
always work out.

1:21:30.515 --> 1:21:32.100
I stood in the way.

1:21:32.142 --> 1:21:34.102
It was me.

1:21:34.144 --> 1:21:36.604
-It wasn't him.
-Let me find him, then.

1:21:36.646 --> 1:21:38.106
He's after me.

1:21:38.148 --> 1:21:39.899
No, he's not.

1:21:39.941 --> 1:21:41.443
Frank.

1:21:41.484 --> 1:21:44.237
-He's not.

1:21:44.279 --> 1:21:46.614
It was the doctor that took him
to your house tonight.

1:21:46.656 --> 1:21:47.991
It wasn't Michael.

1:21:48.033 --> 1:21:50.326
It's not about you.

1:21:51.411 --> 1:21:53.121
-Doctor, get back in the car!
-No!

1:21:53.163 --> 1:21:55.290
I'm still gonna blow
this motherfucker's brains out.

1:21:56.624 --> 1:21:58.668
Mom! Mom!

1:21:59.753 --> 1:22:00.920
Help!

1:22:02.297 --> 1:22:05.133
He's a six-year-old boy
with the strength of a man

1:22:05.175 --> 1:22:06.885
and the mind of an animal.

1:22:06.926 --> 1:22:09.054
I know. I've seen his face.

1:22:09.095 --> 1:22:12.307
I looked in his eyes
when I took off his mask.

1:22:12.349 --> 1:22:14.642
Did you know that
when he was a little boy

1:22:14.684 --> 1:22:17.937
he used to stand
in his sister's bedroom and...

1:22:17.979 --> 1:22:20.148
stare out the window?

1:22:20.190 --> 1:22:22.275
My partner died

1:22:22.317 --> 1:22:24.903
the night he stood
on that same spot.

1:22:24.944 --> 1:22:27.113
But for an instant,

1:22:27.155 --> 1:22:30.367
before his death, he knew.

1:22:30.408 --> 1:22:33.161
Maybe he wasn't looking out.

1:22:34.579 --> 1:22:36.623
Maybe he was looking in.

1:22:38.208 --> 1:22:39.959
At his reflection.

1:22:40.001 --> 1:22:41.795
At himself.

1:22:42.712 --> 1:22:46.383
Who knows what makes him kill,
what motivates him?

1:22:46.424 --> 1:22:51.721
But in his heart,
it always seemed to me

1:22:51.763 --> 1:22:54.641
he wants one thing.

1:22:54.683 --> 1:22:57.268
He's going home.

1:22:57.310 --> 1:22:59.312
-He went from Laurie's
compound... -Mm-hmm.

1:22:59.354 --> 1:23:01.189
...the victims
in her neighborhood,

1:23:01.231 --> 1:23:02.899
to the park, okay?

1:23:02.941 --> 1:23:05.902
If you track those locations,
that's a straight line,

1:23:05.944 --> 1:23:08.029
basically an arrow
pointing straight

1:23:08.071 --> 1:23:11.449
to Lampkin Lane,
Michael's childhood home.

1:23:11.491 --> 1:23:15.412
I came face-to-face with
this asshole when I was a kid.

1:23:15.453 --> 1:23:19.582
He creeps, he kills,
he goes home.

1:23:23.086 --> 1:23:25.714
Then that's where we're going.

1:23:25.755 --> 1:23:27.424
Yeah.

1:23:34.931 --> 1:23:36.808
Karen. Karen.

1:23:36.850 --> 1:23:38.059
Listen, I'm sorry.

1:23:38.101 --> 1:23:39.602
You were right, okay?
I'm sorry.

1:23:39.644 --> 1:23:42.731
Tommy, you took my daughter
to chase a killer,

1:23:42.772 --> 1:23:44.774
and an innocent man is dead.

1:23:44.816 --> 1:23:46.901
Fuck it.
None of us are innocent.

1:23:46.943 --> 1:23:49.112
Karen, listen. Listen.
I fucked up.

1:23:49.154 --> 1:23:50.613
I fucked up. I'm sorry.

1:23:50.655 --> 1:23:52.323
So, what now?

1:23:52.365 --> 1:23:54.701
You're sorry? You're just gonna
stand here hating yourself?

1:23:54.743 --> 1:23:55.869
No.

1:23:55.910 --> 1:23:57.912
I got to keep trying.

1:23:57.954 --> 1:23:59.414
But if I go down,

1:23:59.456 --> 1:24:01.875
I'm gonna go down swinging.

1:24:04.753 --> 1:24:06.629
I need a car.

1:24:07.630 --> 1:24:09.341
I have a car.

1:24:29.069 --> 1:24:31.780
Okay, so the key is
we stick together.

1:24:31.821 --> 1:24:33.448
No, I'm going in alone.

1:24:33.490 --> 1:24:35.116
-What?
-Mr. Elam.

1:24:35.158 --> 1:24:36.993
You fucking dummy,
you brought your kid

1:24:37.035 --> 1:24:38.870
-to the belly of the beast.
-Dad, no.

1:24:38.912 --> 1:24:40.538
Mr. Elam, with all due respect,

1:24:40.580 --> 1:24:42.791
you really expect me
to sit here while you go inside

1:24:42.832 --> 1:24:44.793
and confront the man
that killed my father?

1:24:44.834 --> 1:24:47.212
No, I don't expect you to.

1:24:47.253 --> 1:24:49.464
But I'm asking, Allyson.

1:24:49.506 --> 1:24:51.800
For your sake and my son's.

1:24:51.841 --> 1:24:54.636
Okay? Just stay here.

1:24:54.678 --> 1:24:59.140
You see anything suspicious,
you honk the horn, all right?

1:24:59.182 --> 1:25:01.476
But you stay safe.

1:25:01.518 --> 1:25:03.269
All right?

1:25:07.691 --> 1:25:10.402
I will see you
at the finish line, buddy.

1:26:06.666 --> 1:26:08.251
Okay.

1:26:16.343 --> 1:26:19.304
This is so fucked up.

1:26:23.600 --> 1:26:26.811
-Cameron, let's go.

1:26:26.853 --> 1:26:28.813
Come on.

1:26:28.855 --> 1:26:29.939
Go, go, go, go!

1:26:38.323 --> 1:26:40.700
Okay.

1:26:51.127 --> 1:26:52.879
Dad?

1:27:03.139 --> 1:27:04.766
CAMERON
Allyson.

1:27:04.808 --> 1:27:06.643
Over there.

1:29:39.004 --> 1:29:40.839
Dad.

1:29:45.885 --> 1:29:46.636
Cameron?

1:30:13.496 --> 1:30:15.915
Allyson!

1:30:15.957 --> 1:30:16.958
Cameron!

1:30:25.091 --> 1:30:26.968
Cameron!

1:30:28.219 --> 1:30:29.679
No!

1:30:30.388 --> 1:30:34.017
-Cameron! No!

1:30:35.101 --> 1:30:36.311
Cameron!

1:30:37.604 --> 1:30:39.230
ALLYSON
No.

1:30:39.272 --> 1:30:41.149
No, no, no, no!

1:30:41.191 --> 1:30:43.026
-No!

1:30:43.068 --> 1:30:45.111
-Allyson!
-No!

1:30:48.656 --> 1:30:51.159
Come and get me, motherfucker!

1:30:51.201 --> 1:30:53.286
Come and get me.

1:31:24.192 --> 1:31:25.318
Leave him alone!

1:31:27.070 --> 1:31:28.613
No.

1:31:28.655 --> 1:31:30.490
No. No!

1:31:30.532 --> 1:31:32.867
-No!

1:31:37.038 --> 1:31:38.748
No!

1:31:51.219 --> 1:31:53.763
Do it. Do it.

1:31:54.556 --> 1:31:56.016
Do it!

1:32:16.202 --> 1:32:17.871
Mom.

1:32:31.009 --> 1:32:32.969
Mom.

1:32:39.476 --> 1:32:40.769
No, Mom.

1:32:40.810 --> 1:32:42.270
You want your mask?

1:32:42.312 --> 1:32:43.730
Come and get it!

1:32:43.772 --> 1:32:46.608
You want to fucking
kill someone, take me!

1:32:46.649 --> 1:32:49.319
Mom. No, Mom.

1:32:52.614 --> 1:32:54.574
I'm an innocent woman,

1:32:54.616 --> 1:32:56.618
just like your sister was.

1:32:56.659 --> 1:32:58.661
It was Halloween night.

1:32:58.703 --> 1:33:00.580
She was in her bedroom.

1:33:00.622 --> 1:33:02.791
And it was right here.

1:33:02.832 --> 1:33:04.709
Your house.

1:33:04.751 --> 1:33:07.629
Can't you feel it?

1:33:07.671 --> 1:33:09.631
ALLYSON
No. No, Mom.

1:33:12.717 --> 1:33:14.803
Mom, no.

1:33:21.935 --> 1:33:24.688
Mom!

1:34:03.059 --> 1:34:04.894
Gotcha.

1:34:16.531 --> 1:34:18.491
Hey, Michael.

1:34:18.533 --> 1:34:20.118
It's Halloween.

1:34:20.160 --> 1:34:23.288
Everyone's entitled
to one good scare.

1:35:04.162 --> 1:35:07.374
-- Light him up.
-- Let's take him.

1:35:48.665 --> 1:35:50.250
We got this, Karen.

1:35:51.668 --> 1:35:53.920
Go be with your daughter.

1:36:17.902 --> 1:36:19.904
I always thought Michael Myers

1:36:19.946 --> 1:36:23.992
was flesh and blood,
just like you and me,

1:36:24.034 --> 1:36:25.869
but a mortal man
could not have survived

1:36:25.910 --> 1:36:27.412
what he's lived through.

1:36:28.621 --> 1:36:30.749
The more he kills,

1:36:30.790 --> 1:36:32.500
the more he transcends

1:36:32.542 --> 1:36:36.171
into something else
impossible to defeat.

1:36:36.212 --> 1:36:37.881
Fear.

1:36:37.922 --> 1:36:39.883
People are afraid.

1:36:39.924 --> 1:36:43.261
That is the true curse
of Michael.

1:36:43.303 --> 1:36:46.014
He'll always be here, won't he?

1:36:46.056 --> 1:36:48.224
Even when we can't see him.

1:36:54.272 --> 1:36:56.566
You can't defeat it
with brute force.

1:36:58.068 --> 1:37:01.196
If we only knew then
what we know now.

1:37:39.317 --> 1:37:41.569
It is the essence of evil.

1:37:43.655 --> 1:37:45.573
The anchor that divides us.

1:37:46.908 --> 1:37:50.620
It is the terror that grows
stronger when we try to hide.

1:38:23.903 --> 1:38:26.448
If they don't stop him tonight,

1:38:26.489 --> 1:38:28.783
maybe we'll find him tomorrow.

1:38:28.825 --> 1:38:30.368
Or next Halloween,

1:38:30.410 --> 1:38:34.039
when the sun sets
and someone is alone.

1:39:10.575 --> 1:39:14.162
You can't close your eyes
and pretend he isn't there.

1:39:19.209 --> 1:39:21.503
Because he is.
